Class JsonHttpClient

JSON HTTP Client.

Implementation is not thread-safe.

@since 1.6 @author Ravi Mistry @deprecated (scheduled to be removed in 1.1314) Use HttpTransport instead.

Class JsonHttpParser

Parses HTTP JSON response content into an data class of key/value pairs.

Implementation is thread-safe.

Sample usage: 

 
  static void setParser(HttpRequest request) {
    request.addParser(new JsonHttpParser(new JacksonFactory()));
  }
@since 1.0 @author Yaniv Inbar @deprecated (scheduled to be removed in 1.1314) Use JsonObjectParser instead.
Class JsonHttpRequest

JSON HTTP request to JsonHttpClient.

Implementation is not thread-safe.

@since 1.6 @author Ravi Mistry @deprecated (scheduled to be removed in 1.1314) Use HttpRequest instead.
Class JsonHttpRequestInitializer

JSON HTTP request initializer.

For example, this might be used to set prettyPrint and api key: 

   public class BooksRequestInitializer implements JsonHttpRequestInitializer {
     public void initialize(JsonHttpRequest request) {
       BooksRequest booksRequest = (BooksRequest)request;
       booksRequest.setPrettyPrint(true);
       booksRequest.setKey(API_KEY);
     }
   }

Implementations should normally be thread-safe.

@since 1.6 @author Ravi Mistry @deprecated (scheduled to be removed in 1.1314) Use HttpRequestInitializer instead.
